<p>
<b>Budget and Taxation: Government Waste 
</b>
</center>
<ul>
<b>Books:</b>
<p>
<a href="/heritage/congress/chapt1.html">How Congress Won the Budget War</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/utt.html">Ronald D. Utt, Ph.D.</a>. (<i>Reviewing the Revolution: Conservative Successes in the 104th Congress</i>)<br>

<a href="/heritage/issues96/chpt1.html">Budget</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/hodge.htm">Scott A. Hodge</a>.  (<i>Issues '96: The Candidate's Briefing Book</i>)<br>
<a href="/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/1980s.html">What Really Happened in the 1980s?</a> by Peter J. Ferrara. (<i>Issues '94: The Candidate's Briefing Book</i>)
<p>
<b>Policy Papers:</b>
<p>
<li>10/15/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/bg1095.html">Reinvention Has Not Ended the "Era of Big Government"</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/hodge.htm">Scott A. Hodge</a>. (Backgrounder #1095)



<li>10/15/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/fyi123.html">How Government Wastes Your Money: Report No. 3</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/utt.html">Ronald D. Utt, Ph.D.</a> and Daniel J. Hickey. (F.Y.I. #123)


<li>7/25/96 <a href="http://www.townhall.com/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/fyi113.html">Clinton Takes Undeserved Credit For Congress's Deficit Reduction</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/hodge.htm">Scott A. Hodge</a>. (F.Y.I. #113)

<li>7/23/96 <a href="http://www.heritage.org/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/fyi112.html">How Government Wastes Your Money: Report No. 2</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/utt.html">Ronald D. Utt, Ph.D.</a> (F.Y.I. #112) 


<li>6/17/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/fyi109.html">How Congress Won the Budget War</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/utt.html">Ronald D. Utt</a>. (F.Y.I. #109)
<li>6/1/96 <a href="/heritage/resource_bank/injun6fe.html">Your Right to Know</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/feulner.html">Edwin J. Feulner, Jr.</a>. (June 1996 <i>Insider</i>)

<LI>5/31/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/fyi105.html">How the Government Wastes Your Money: Report No. 1</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/utt.html">Ronald D. Utt</a>. (F.Y.I. #105) 


<li>5/30/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/bgup278.html">Clinton's
 Unbalanced Federal Employment Policy</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/spring.htm
">Baker Spring</a> and <a href="/heritage/staff/barry.html">John S. Barry</a>.  (Backgrounder Update No. 278)<li>5/28/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/ib225.html">How S. 729 Would Set Back Transportation Reform and Block Fiscal Oversight</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/utt.html">Ronald D. Utt</a>. (Issue Bulletin #225)
