<title>Publications Library
 -- Heritage </title>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">
<center><h2><font size=+3>T</font>he <font size=+3>H</font>eritage <font size=+3>F</font>oundation</h2></center>
<center><h3><font size=+2>P</font>ublications <font size=+2>L</font>ibrary</h3>
<hr size=3 width=50%>
<p>
<b>National Security: NATO
</b>
</center>
<p>
<ul>
<b>Books:</b>
<p>
<a href="/heritage/congress/chapt7.html">How the 104th Congress Has Protected the Nation's Security</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/moore.html">Thomas Moore</a>. (<i>Reviewing the Revolution: Conservative Successes in the 104th Congress</i>)<p>
<b>Policy Papers:</b>
<p>

<li>3/1/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/forpol/cbrief23.html">NATO Expansion: Myths and Realities</a> by  W. Bruce Weinrod. (Committee Brief #23) 
<li>2/7/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/forpol/bg1067.html">Getting NATO Back to Basics</a> by John Hillen. (Backgrounder #1067) 
<li>10/26/95 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/forpol/lect544.html">Rebirth, Return, Reunion: Hungary's Euro-Atlantic Agenda</a> by His Excellency Arpad Goncz, President of the Republic of Hungary. (Lecture #544)
<li>10/6/95 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/lect542.html">National Defense and America's Alliances</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/holmes.htm">Kim R. Holmes</a>. (Heritage Lecture #542) 
</ul>
<p>
