<HEAD>
<title>Bradley, White to Attend Aspen Summit 96 -- PFF</title>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/pff/notebook.gif" LINK="#8C1717" VLINK="#545454" ALINK="#FF0000"> 
<blockquote><ul>
<a href="/pff/"><img src="/pff/pffdoc.gif" align="right" border="0"></a>
For Immediate Release<BR>
June 25, 1996<BR>
Contact: Rick ODonnell<BR>
202/289-8928<BR>
NEWS RELEASE
<p>
<h2>Bradley, White to Attend Aspen Summit 96</h2>

Senator Bill Bradley (D-NJ) and Representative Rick White (R-WA) will be among the participants at the Aspen Summit this August 5-6, The Progress & Freedom Foundation announced today.  The Summit will explore whether America's future in the digital age will be one of progress or decay.
<p>
White, who is chairman of the Congressional Internet Caucus, and Bradley, who recently completed a tour promoting his new book <b>Time Present, Time Past</b>, will be among the more than 30 participants at the Summit.  Also attending will be author Alvin Toffler, PBS commentator David Gergen, ACLU president Nadine Strossen, author George Gilder, John Gage of Sun Microsystems, and author David Gelernter.
<p>
"A recurring theme in this election year is the insecurity Americans feel about their future," said Foundation president Jeffrey A. Eisenach.  "The Summit will examine how America can best cope with the transition to a new society  how to make the transition less painful and more productive for all Americans."
<p>
The Summit, to be held at the Ritz-Carlton Hotel in Aspen, Colo., will also feature a debate on whether the growth of the Internet is a "Leading Cultural Indicator of Progress." Participants will include Edwin Diamond and Stephen Bates, authors of "Smash the Internet" (<i>Weekly Standard</i>, Oct. 30, 1995), G.A. (Jay) Keyworth, former Science Advisor to President Reagan, and Esther Dyson, president of EDventure Holdings.
<p>
Four working groups at the Summit will explore what government policies should be pursued to ensure continued progress toward a better future in the digital age.  Former FCC Commissioner Dennis Patrick will highlight a session on regulatory convergence and Shira Perlmutter, Associate Register for International Affairs and Policy at the Copyright Office, will highlight a session on intellectual property.
<p>
A private, non-profit, non-partisan idea center established in 1993, The Progress & Freedom Foundation aims to create a positive vision of the future founded in the historic principles of the American Idea. 	
<p>
