Keleher, Robert E., William N. Cox, and William P. Orzechowski. 1982.  "The Flat-Rate Income Tax: Boon or Boondoggle?" <I>Economic Review</I>, Federal Reserve Bank of Atlanta
     (September), pp. 24-30.
<blockquote>
          Points out that flat-rate tax is system most compatible
          with classical political economy.  Finds support in
          works of Adam Smith, John Stuart Mill and others.
</blockquote><p>
Kirkland, Richard I. 1982.  "The Flatter-Tax Movement Picks Up Steam."  <i>Fortune</i> (July 26), pp. 33-35.
