Laffer, Arthur B. 1986.  "The Complete Flat Tax."  In Victor A. Canto, Charles W. Kadlec, and Arthur B. Laffer, eds., <i>The Financial Analysts Guide to Fiscal Policy</i>.  New York:
     Praeger, pp. 108-140.
<blockquote>
          Proposes elimination of all federal taxes, not just the
          individual income tax, with a flat 11.5% rate on
          individuals plus a value-added tax on businesses.
</blockquote><p>
Landsburg, Steven E. 1994.  "Let's Make Taxes Really Flat."  <i>Forbes</i> (December 19), p. 170.
<p>
Lee, Susan. 1982.  "Rating the Flat-Rate Tax."  <i>Wall Street Journal</i> (June 30).
<blockquote>
          Points out that while there may be winners and losers
          under a flat-rate, the current system also has winners
          and losers.  Believes that a flat-rate is preferable
          because it would stimulate growth.
</blockquote><p>
Lehrman, Lewis E. 1985.  "A Flat Tax Would Stimulate Growth."  <i>New York Times</i> (February 24).
