Lindsey, Lawrence B. 1990.  <i>The Growth Experiment: How the New Tax Policy Is Transforming the U.S. Economy</i>.  New York:
     Basic Books, pp. 227-240.
<blockquote>
          Presents a proposal for a 19% flat-rate tax system.
</blockquote><p>
Long, Russell B. 1982.  "Flat-Rate Tax Would Help the Rich."  <i>Washington Post</i> (July 13).
<blockquote>
          A former chairman of the Senate Finance Committee
          points out that most tax loopholes actually provide tax
          relief for the middle class.  Thus elimination of
          loopholes in favor of lower rates will mainly help the
          rich.
</blockquote><p>
Lucas, J.R. 1984.  "Towards a Theory of Taxation."  <i>Social
     Philosophy and Policy</i>, vol. 2, no. 1 (Autumn), pp. 161-173.
<blockquote>
          A professor of philosophy at Oxford argues against
          using the tax system for redistribution and for lower
          tax rates on philosophical grounds.
</blockquote><p>
