McKenzie, Richard. 1982.  "A Case Against the Flat-Rate Tax."  <i>Washington Times</i> (October 20).
<blockquote>
          A professor of economics at Clemson believes that
          elimination of tax deductions, even if rates are
          lowered, would ultimately lead to higher taxes. 
          Believes that a narrow tax base prevents government
          from raising taxes as much as it would like.  See also
          McCaleb (1985).
</blockquote><p>
Merrill, Peter, Ken Wertz, and Shvetank Shah. 1995.  "Corporate Tax Liability Under the USA and Flat Taxes."  <i>Tax Notes</i>,
