<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>Town Hall Spotlight: The Balanced Budget - Jan 1996</TITLE>

</HEAD>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/paper2.jpg">  
<P>

<CENTER>
<img src="/townhall/spotlights/budget/budgspot.gif">
<br><H2>The Balanced Budget: Will We Ever See It?</CENTER></H2>

Balancing the Budget is a priority of the conservative revolution that swept through Congress in 1994, but so far, the President has impeded the budget process with his vetos.  What could have been done by conservatives in just a few weeks, is now turning into a year long process.  Some pundits are even now predicting that Clinton won't make a deal and take the issue to the voters in November.<P>
Town Hall will keep up on the details and bring them to you as they happen in the Budget Spotlight. Check here often more the lastest news, polls, and opinion as the nation debates the balanced budget.
<P>
If you are interested in having your information posted here, send your press releases
to <a href="mailto:budget@townhall.com">budget@townhall.com</a>. 
<b>Priority is given to documents already in HTML format.</b>
<P>
<P>
<HR>
<P><a name="week"></a>

<CENTER><h2><a name="Misc">The Balanced Budget</a></h2> <br>

</center><p>

<p>
<ul>
